quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  47,12,"Indeed, Allah enters those who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds into Gardens beneath which rivers flow. And those who have denied enjoy themselves and eat as cattle eat, but the Fire is a dwelling for them."
  47,13,"And how many a town was more powerful than your town{1}which evicted you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>? We annihilated them, and there was no helper for them.",footnotes:1:Addressing Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) about the town which evicted him (Makkah).
  47,14,"Is someone who relies on evident proof from his Lord like someone the evil of whose work was adorned for him? And they{1}followed their own whims.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from singular to plural.
  47,15,"The likeness of the Garden<i class=""s"">(of Paradise) </i>that the mindful<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a><i class=""s"">(of God) </i>have been promised: rivers of water, <span class=""h"">not</span>staling<sup foot_note=""81171"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup>; and rivers of milk whose taste has not changed; and rivers of wine, a delight for those who drink; and rivers of honey, clarified and pure. And they have therein of all products and forgiveness from their Lord.<i class=""s"">(How can this be) </i>compared to the fate of those abiding in the Fire and were given, for drink, scalding water, so that it tore their bowels?"
  47,16,"And among them is one who listens to you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, but when they{1}depart from your presence, they say to those given knowledge, “What did he say just now?” Those are the ones whose hearts Allah has sealed, and they followed their own whims.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from singular to plural. The difference between this shift and the one in sign number 14 should be pondered by the reader.
  47,17,"But as for those who wanted guidance, He has increased them in guidance and has brought them their mindfulness<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>."
  47,18,"So are they but waiting until the Hour comes to them suddenly? In fact, its tokens have already come. But how will they be reminded when it has come to them?"
  47,19,"So know<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>that there is no god but Allah, and ask forgiveness for your misdeed, and for believing men and believing women. For Allah knows your moving about and your dwelling."
